      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a small knob of<strong> butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until the onion has softened and caramelised – this is your <strong>caramelised onion</strong></p><p>While the onion is cooking, wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
